Even with the look-ahead bias I have it doesn’t look promising. Lets see the result if we just lay the favorites instead of betting on the underdog. Laying the favorites means a success for every Draw/Win for the selected team.

I guess not significant. Lets check

sum(dbinom(c(19:65), 65, prob = 0.25))

[1] 0.2552148

It seems more steady and less volatily than betting over only one outcome (selected team to win the match). Before I’ll test this strategy over other leagues, I’d like to guesstimate how many matches needed before the Goals Per Possession parameter “converge” to its true value. I’ll plot the running GFPerPoss over the course of the season for each team. Suprisingly, unlike pandas, there is no rolling function in R so I had to create one

rolling_mean <- function(x) {
  output <- array(dim = length(x))
  for (i in 1:length(x)) {
    output[i] = sum(x[1:i])/i
  }
  return(output)
}

So I think it is safe to use the GFPerPoss from match day 15 onwards. Now on to testing if this strategy may work in Laliga
